---
import "../styles/site.css";
---

<html lang="pl">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Postmerce - publish once, adapt everywhere</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Postmerce is a private-first publishing system for video content across social platforms."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="page-shell">
      <nav class="topbar" aria-label="Primary">
        <a class="brand" href="/">Postmerce</a>
        <div class="nav-links">
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
          <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
          <a href="/data-deletion">Data deletion</a>
        </div>
      </nav>

      <section class="hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">One video. Many platforms. Controlled publishing.</p>
        <h1>Postmerce turns one social asset into platform-specific posts.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          A lean publishing system for uploading video, preparing per-platform captions,
          scheduling jobs and tracking every target without SaaS overhead.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button" href="mailto:support@postmerce.pl">Contact support</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="https://staging.postmerce.pl">Private staging</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="feature-grid" aria-label="Product pillars">
        <article>
          <span>01</span>
          <h2>Private first</h2>
          <p>Built for Wojtek's own publishing loop before customer accounts, teams or billing.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>02</span>
          <h2>Queue based</h2>
          <p>HTTP requests create jobs. Workers publish, retry and keep platform failures isolated.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>03</span>
          <h2>SaaS ready</h2>
          <p>The core stays clean enough to grow into a product when the private loop proves value.</p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
